Radar Charts
 
A radar chart is useful when you're trying to visually represent a dimension along three or more measure axes that have different scales.

Create a Radar Chart

In the lens, click  and then select the Metrics Radar chart type.
Add at least three measures. For example, add average opportunity amount, total opportunity amount, and count of rows.
Add the dimension to analyze the measures by. For example, select Account Type.
To change the chart display, click  and set the chart properties in the Formatting panel.

Use a metrics radar chart instead of a stacked bar chart when the measures are similar across groupings.
